00:00:55.740 --> 00:00:59.250
And this is sort of the
subject of master equation

00:00:59.250 --> 00:01:03.460
open system dynamics, and
this cartoon sort of tells you

00:01:03.460 --> 00:01:05.489
what you want to do.

00:01:05.489 --> 00:01:10.990
We have a total system, which is
one part we are interested in,

00:01:10.990 --> 00:01:14.163
and the other one, often it has
many, many degrees of freedom,

00:01:14.163 --> 00:01:16.140
and we don't want to
keep track of them.

00:01:16.140 --> 00:01:18.380
But they have one Hamiltonian.

00:01:18.380 --> 00:01:22.330
But we are only interested in
how our atomic system evolves,

00:01:22.330 --> 00:01:24.550
