00:13:37.020 --> 00:13:39.195
a and b are the two input nodes.

00:13:42.240 --> 00:13:46.540
And the angle of
the beam splitter,

00:13:46.540 --> 00:13:49.700
which interpolates between
0% and 100% reflection

00:13:49.700 --> 00:13:52.180
transmission is theta.

00:13:52.180 --> 00:13:55.090
And we're now looking
for the output

00:13:55.090 --> 00:13:58.010
state of the total system.

00:13:58.010 --> 00:14:00.190
We're not performing
the measurement yet,

00:14:00.190 --> 00:14:08.330
and this is now acting on
the total system, which

00:14:08.330 --> 00:14:11.110
