that suddenly the vacuum

00:27:02.830 --> 00:27:04.760
Is no longer in
the vacuum state.

00:27:04.760 --> 00:27:06.770
Or in the case of
spontaneous emission,

00:27:06.770 --> 00:27:10.500
the vacuum can just take as many
photons as you dumping into it.

00:27:10.500 --> 00:27:14.120
They disappear so quickly that
for all practical purposes,

00:27:14.120 --> 00:27:18.380
the environment stays
in the vacuum state.

00:27:18.380 --> 00:27:20.300
So this is called the
Bohr approximation.

00:27:20.300 --> 00:27:22.390
The environment is not changing.

00:27:22.390 --> 00:27:25.851
It has enough capacity you to
be modified by the measurement

00:27:25.851 --> 00:27:26.350
