01:08:16.990 --> 01:08:30.140
Whenever we have some
damping of the population,

01:08:30.140 --> 01:08:33.170
the coherence is only
damped with a factor of 1/2.

01:08:37.740 --> 01:08:40.479
One way to explain it
in a very simple way

01:08:40.479 --> 01:08:57.750
is, that if you have an
amplitude alpha excited

01:08:57.750 --> 01:09:06.260
and alpha ground, the
population in the excited state

01:09:06.260 --> 01:09:09.180
is this squared.

01:09:09.180 --> 01:09:13.470
So you sometimes make the
model that the amplitude decays

01:09:13.470 --> 01:09:17.319
with gamma over 2,
but the population

01:09:17.319 --> 01:09:22.290
is-- because you take the
product, decays with gamma.

01:09:22.290 --> 01:09:27.580
So you would say alpha
e and alpha g both decay

01:09:27.580 --> 01:09:30.200
with half the rate,
but the probability

01:09:30.200 --> 01:09:33.689
is for the total rate,
and the coherence

01:09:33.689 --> 01:09:37.109
is the product of
the amplitudes.

01:09:37.109 --> 01:09:39.750
So therefore when you
look at the coherence,

01:09:39.750 --> 01:09:42.680
this decays with 1/2 gamma e.

01:09:42.680 --> 01:09:46.350
This decays with 1/2 gamma g,
and this is what you get here,

01:09:46.350 --> 01:09:51.120
1/2 gamma in state a,
1/2 gamma in state b.

01:09:51.120 --> 01:09:54.160
Whereas the probability
to be in this state

01:09:54.160 --> 01:09:59.370
decays with twice that because
the probability is squared.

01:09:59.370 --> 01:10:03.190
So you find that pretty much
in any quantum mechanically

01:10:03.190 --> 01:10:05.420
corrects derivation,
which you do

01:10:05.420 --> 01:10:07.515
about the decay of
population coherences.

